## Commands
```
make setup      — Initialize environment
make lint       — Lint check
make lint-fix   — Auto-fix lint issues
make format     — Auto format
make typecheck  — Type check
make test       — Run tests
make check      — Full check (lint + typecheck + test)
{% if needs_server -%}
make dev        — Start dev server
make test-e2e   — End-to-end test
{% endif -%}
```

## Project Structure
{% if is_python -%}
- `src/{{ project_slug }}/` — Source code
{% elif is_typescript -%}
- `src/` — Source code
{% endif -%}
- `tests/` — Tests mirroring src

## Workflow
1. Plan first, implement second.
2. Write tests first, then implement.
3. Run `make check` before commit.

## Boundaries
### Always
- Strict types · Tests for new modules · Files < 300 lines
- Commits: `type(scope): description` (≤200 chars)

### Ask First
- New dependencies · CI changes · Public API deletion

### Never
- No hardcoded secrets
{% if is_python -%}
- No `type: ignore` without comment
{% else -%}
- No `@ts-ignore` or `any`
{% endif -%}
- No skipping pre-commit hooks
